---
import ContentLayout from '@/layouts/content-layout.astro'
---

<ContentLayout
	title="Chef Booking Marketplace — Ilzam"
	description="Two-sided marketplace built in 10 weeks by one engineer. Go, React, PostgreSQL, Stripe Connect. Private chef booking platform in Scandinavia."
>
	<a href="/work" class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">&larr; All work</a>

	<div class="mt-6 flex items-center justify-between">
		<span class="rounded-sm bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium uppercase">Marketplace</span>
		<span class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Scandinavia / 2024</span>
	</div>

	<h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-light leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
		Chef Booking Marketplace
	</h1>
	<p class="mt-2 text-lg text-muted-foreground">
		Two-sided marketplace, 10 weeks, one engineer.
	</p>

	<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
		{["Go", "React", "PostgreSQL", "Stripe Connect", "Redis"].map((tech) => (
			<span class="rounded-full border px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs">{tech}</span>
		))}
	</div>

	<!-- Content sections — customize freely -->
	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Challenge</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			A Scandinavian startup needed a platform to connect customers with private chefs for home dining experiences. They needed a two-sided marketplace with real-time availability, secure payments, and chef profile management — built fast enough to validate the concept before their runway ran out.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Approach</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			I chose Go for the backend — fast, simple, and easy to deploy. React for the customer-facing frontend. PostgreSQL for relational data (bookings, availability, chef profiles). Stripe Connect for marketplace payments so chefs get paid directly. Redis for session management and caching availability slots.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			No microservices. No over-engineering. A clean monolith that could be deployed on a single server and scaled later if the business proved out.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Key Decisions</h2>
		<ul class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-muted-foreground">
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Stripe Connect over building payments in-house.</span>
				Marketplace payments are complex — splits, refunds, payouts to multiple parties. Stripe Connect handled this out of the box. Saved at least 3 weeks of development.
			</li>
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Monolith over microservices for V1.</span>
				At this stage, deployment simplicity matters more than architectural purity. One binary, one database, one deployment target.
			</li>
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Real-time availability with Redis.</span>
				Chef availability needed to be fast and conflict-free. Redis provided the speed for checking and locking time slots during the booking flow.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Result</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			Shipped to production in 10 weeks as a solo engineer. The platform launched with chef onboarding, customer search and booking, Stripe-powered payments, and a review system. The client had paying customers within the first month of launch.
		</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Related -->
	<section class="mt-12 border-t pt-8">
		<h3 class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">Related Notes</h3>
		<ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
			<li><a href="/notes/stripe-connect-marketplace-gotchas" class="text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground">Stripe Connect Marketplace Gotchas</a></li>
			<li><a href="/notes/go-vs-node-rest-api-startup" class="text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground">Go vs Node for REST APIs in Startups</a></li>
			<li><a href="/notes/how-much-does-mvp-cost" class="text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground">How Much Does an MVP Cost?</a></li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<!-- CTA -->
	<section class="mt-10 rounded-lg bg-muted/50 p-6 text-center">
		<p class="font-medium">Building a marketplace?</p>
		<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
			I've shipped this in production. If you want a second opinion on your approach, book a technical call.
		</p>
		<a
			href="https://cal.com/ilzam/technical"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
			class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-foreground px-5 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-background transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
		>
			Book a Technical Call
		</a>
	</section>
</ContentLayout>
